<%- include('partials/header') %>

<div class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-text">
        <span class="hero-eyebrow">Need Help?</span>
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p>Everything you need to know before your visit to Wild Nature Park. Can't find your answer? <a href="/contact" style="color:#E8900A;">Contact us</a>.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="faq-list">

    <div class="faq-category-title">Planning Your Visit</div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
            What are your opening times?
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            Wild Nature Park is open <strong>every day of the year</strong> from <strong>9:00 AM to 6:00 PM</strong>.
            Last entry is at <strong>5:00 PM</strong>. This includes Bank Holidays, weekends and school holidays.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
            Is there parking available?
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            Yes — we have a large free car park directly on site, with accessible spaces located close to the main entrance.
            We also have dedicated coach parking and a drop-off zone.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
            Is the park wheelchair accessible?
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            Absolutely. All habitats, experience areas, pathways, cafés and facilities are fully wheelchair accessible.
            Mobility scooters and wheelchairs are available to hire at the main entrance.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
            Can I bring my dog?
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            Only registered assistance dogs are permitted inside the park. This is to ensure the safety and
            wellbeing of our wildlife residents.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-category-title">Food &amp; Facilities</div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
            Is there food available in the park?
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            Yes! We have two dining options — <strong>The Canopy Café</strong> (light lunches, snacks, hot drinks)
            and the <strong>Savannah Grill</strong> (hot meals, burgers, vegetarian options). Both are open throughout
            the day. Picnic areas are also available across the park.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
            Are there baby changing facilities?
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            Yes, baby changing rooms are available in all toilet blocks across the park. We also have a
            family rest room near the main entrance with feeding facilities.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-category-title">Wildlife &amp; Experiences</div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
            Can I take photos with the animals?
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            Photography is welcomed and encouraged throughout the entire park. Several close-encounter experiences
            such as Giraffe Encounter and Tropical Bird Feeding offer exceptional photo opportunities with our rangers.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
            How long does it take to see the whole park?
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            We recommend allowing a <strong>full day</strong> to experience everything. Most visitors spend 5–7 hours
            exploring the five habitats and attending experiences. You could easily return for more!
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question">
            Are the animal encounters safe?
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
            All experiences are supervised by our expert keepers and rangers. The safety of both our guests and animals
            is our absolute top priority. Full briefings are given before every encounter activity.
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<div class="faq-cta">
    <p>Still have a question?</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Our Team &rarr;</a>
</div>

<script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-question').forEach(q => {
        q.addEventListener('click', () => {
            const item = q.parentElement;
            const answer = q.nextElementSibling;
            const isOpen = item.classList.contains('open');
            document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(i => {
                i.classList.remove('open');
                i.querySelector('.faq-answer').classList.remove('active');
            });
            if (!isOpen) {
                item.classList.add('open');
                answer.classList.add('active');
            }
        });
    });
</script>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>